Considering you have gone through the tutorial and have all the dependencies installed, let's go ahead and spawn our model in the Gazebo.
You need to install "urdf files for the robot" in your system from the main Github Repository.
In the catkin_ws/src folder, you need to create a package as follows:
                        catkin_ws/src$ catkin_create_pkg armpi_fpv rospy
Move the "meshes" and "armpi_fpv.urdf" in the "armpi_fpc/src" folder.
Move out of the "src" folder using "cd .."
Now in the catkin_ws folder run "catkin_make" in the terminal. You will see some activity happening in the terminal.
Source the file using "source devel/setup.bash" in the same folder.
Now launch your robot using " roslaunch armpi_fpv spawn_urdf.launch"



